user.biography: Welcome to the official Visit California Instagram feed. Use #VisitCalifornia for a chance to be featured.

node.text:
Teresa Baker is building a more inclusive future for the outdoor industry. In this story from @theoutbound, follow her journey as she and a group of diverse outdoor leaders become some of the first members of the public to explore #HaroldRichardsonRedwoodsReserve. It's a massive old-growth redwood grove recently protected by @savetheredwoods in @SonomaCounty.
.
#VisitCalifornia #EveryoneOutside

node.text:
The largest municipal park in the country, #GriffithPark in @discoverla has 53 miles of trails to hike and is made up of 4,300 acres of jaw-dropping views. Here are the five things you have to do when you're there! ⁣
.⁣
#VisitCalifornia #discoverLA

node.title: 5 Amazing Things to Do at Griffith Park

Made up of five islands off the Southern California coast, @channelislandsnps is an adventurer's dream! You can kayak, hike, and watch sea animals, like the humpback whale, in their natural habitat. #California101⁣
⁣
What else do you love to do at #ChannelIslandsNationalPark?⁣
.⁣
#VisitCalifornia

node.text:
Let's take a moment to appreciate the trails and facilities that make the outdoors more accessible for everyone. ⁣If you're celebrating #DisabilityPrideMonth and have tips or recommendations based on your own experience, let us know and we'll be sure to pass it on. ⁣
⁣
🌳 Parks including @YosemiteNPS, @sequoiakingsnps, Clear Lake State Park and Montaña de Oro State Park have upgraded some of their trails and campsites to make them wheelchair-accessible. ⁣
🧏🏼‍♀️ @seaworldsandiego can arrange an American sign language interpreter for shows and tours. In addition, @YosemiteNPS and @sequoiakingsnps also offer sign language interpreting and assistive listening devices for park programs. ⁣
🌊 @VisitSanDiego offers free manual or power beach wheelchairs at a number of popular beaches. @SurfCityUSA has rolled out a wheelchair-accessible mat that leads to the water's edge. ⁣
⁣
📷: @wonders_within_reach, @clanhuntington
.⁣
#VisitCalifornia

node.text:
Traveling with little ones or furry friends? Alli and Bobby Talley, the duo behind the @traveling_newlyweds blog have a few tricks to share, having hit the road with their one-year-old son, Jude and 70-pound bernedoodle, Sally.⁣
⁣
🥾 Find destinations that are pedestrian-friendly like @VisitBigBear: "It's this little mountain town that has a lot of character and a lot of charm."⁣
🐶 Consider your dog's comfort and safety: "The key to traveling with a dog, especially really long distances, is being organized and giving them space to feel like they're not stuck on this tiny little seat," Bobby says. Also, make sure your dog wears a safety restraint. ⁣
🏨 For dog-friendly lodgings, the Talleys suggest @laquintahotels and @kimpton. "Kimpton hotels will supply your room with dog bowls, and a lot of times they'll give you dog treats," Alli says. They also host regular happy hours where your pooch is also invited. ⁣
⁣
For more local tips, check our link in bio. ⁣
⁣
📷 : @traveling_newlyweds⁣ at @solvangusa and @visitlaguna 
.⁣
#VisitCalifornia

Wanna meet Black Widow, Captain Marvel or Iron Man? Best head to the brand new #AvengersCampus at @disneyland's California Adventure Park in @VisitAnaheim! As well as the opportunity to meet your Marvel heroes, you may even spot Spiderman doing flips atop the Stark Motors Building. ⁣
⁣
And lunch will be just as interesting. The menu at Pym Test Kitchen reflects the super-sized and miniaturized creations of Ant-Man and The Wasp: think giant (or tiny) soft pretzels, a huge chicken filet sandwich with an extra-petite bun, or the family-friendly Pym-ini sandwich with salami, provolone and focaccia, sized to feed up to eight people.⁣
⁣
Have you visited yet? What was your standout? ⁣
⁣
Check our link in bio for more info on the campus. ⁣
⁣
📷 : @wingchunjourney, @lvitz, @defloresyviajes⁣
.⁣
#VisitCalifornia

@VisitSacramento isn't called America's Farm-to-Fork Capital for nothing! There are 80 craft breweries in the region, 12 Michelin-rated restaurants and 20+ farmers markets. So, work up an appetite before you go, and bookmark these must-sees: ​
⁣
🍻  Drink: Beer on the patio at @fieldworkbrewing_sacramento⁣.
🍽  Eat: Michelin-starred shared plates @canoneastsac. ⁣
👀  See: Sacramento's many murals (nearly 800) on a self-guided walking tour. ⁣
🛏. Stay: At the newly-opened @fortsutterhotel ⁣
⁣
📷. : @goodthompson, @allthethings_liz, @eatswithmandy, @lucatomatillo
.⁣
#VisitCalifornia #VisitSacramento

Grab your helmet; we're going cycling at @officialvisitdavis in @VisitYolo. With 100 miles of cycling lanes lining the city, we promise you'll be in good company! Here's how to spend a day in the college town: ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
🚲 Loop through the lush @ucdavis_arboretum⁣⁣. 
🚲 Pedal along streets lined with shops, galleries and restaurants in downtown Davis. ⁣⁣
🚲 Time your trip to coincide with @davis.farmers.market on Wednesdays and Saturdays at Central Park, and enjoy your market wins with a picnic. ⁣⁣

Any other suggestions? 
⁣
📷 : @sal.op, @marilynmaciel, @officialvisitdavis
.⁣⁣
#VisitCalifornia #visitdavis

node.text:
The @skunktrain goes back to 1885. Not in a time travel kind of way, though the view has been mostly unchanged for a century, so kind of. You can catch it between @VisitFortBraggCA and Willits, with an amazing view of @northofordinaryca's lush redwood groves along the way. ⁣
⁣
And what's with the name, you ask? Locals began calling it Skunk Train back in 1925, in reference to the odor caused by gasoline fumes and potbelly stoves. 🦨⁣
⁣
You can take the old-school train, or pedal it up with the Skunk Train Rail bikes. Whichever option you choose, we can guarantee it'll be glorious. ⁣
⁣
📷 : @thechickenpapa, @travelwithtraut⁣
.⁣
#VisitCalifornia #NorthCoast

node.text:
Imagine waking up among towering redwood trees, the tumbling Kings River, or a dazzling desert-night sky filled with stars. Well, no need to imagine – these centrally located lodgings and campgrounds mean you can extend your playtime with an overnight stay at our national parks. ⁣
⁣
⛺️ @RedwoodNPS: Sleep among the ancient trees at Crescent City's Fern Hook Cabins or in a log cabin at Redwoods @kampgroundsofamerica. ⁣
⛺️ @PinnaclesNPS: Pinnacles has no hotels, and the only campground is the privately run Pinnacles Campground, which has plenty of summer dates available.⁣
⛺️ @sequoiakingsnps: Sleep to the sound of the Kings River at Cedar Grove Lodge, then get up early to hike to Mist Falls or stroll around Zumwalt Meadow. ⁣
⛺️ @JoshuaTreeNPS: Camping is the only in-park option here, and you'll need to reserve in advance for sites at Black Rock, Jumbo Rocks, or Ryan campgrounds. Hidden Valley Campground is first-come, first-served.⁣
⁣
Check our link in bio for more ideas. ⁣
⁣
📷 : @scenery.seekers at @PinnaclesNPS⁣
.⁣
#VisitCalifornia
